### Addition 1 — New handler function (~line 1633)

Insert `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3` between the end of `common_chat_extra_context()` (line 1632) and the start of `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (line 1634):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & /* tmpl */,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                std::string user_content = system_prompt.empty()
                    ? content
                    : system_prompt + "\n" + content;
                data.prompt += "<s>[INST] " + user_content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

Key pattern decisions: `tmpl` is unused (prompt is built manually), `msg.value("role","")` / `msg.value("content","")` matches the project's JSON access idiom, `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` is used as specified.

