### Addition 2 — Detection block (just before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690)

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // Absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT] distinguishes this from the Ministral 3 handler above
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

The `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`-absent check is the critical discriminator — Ministral 3 (already handled first) requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be present, so there's no ambiguity.
